Author: PARTRIDGE
Vol / Page: 287
Edition:
Quote: Although, he said, he was the white-haired boy with the trump he was due for a shake-up and he had to take a tumble to himself as to how he gave the company-rations away.
Notes:

Date: 0/0/1937
Source: Dictionary of Slang
Author: PARTRIDGE
Vol / Page: 954
Edition:
Quote: <i>White-haired boy</i>. is an Australian and New Zealand variant of the next entry: late C. 19-20. Whence <i>you must have white hairs</i>, a New Zealand c.p. to a man getting an unexpected favour: C. 20.
Notes:

Date: 0/0/1988
Source: Dictionary of Kiwi Slang, A
Author: McGILL
Vol / Page: 123
Edition:
Quote: <i>white-haired boy</i> darling or favourite, antipodean variant of `white-headed boy', with reference to the fair hair of babies. -<i> you must have white hairs</i> said to somebody receiving an unexpected favour. <i>[Partridge]</i>
